				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\upvarepsilon }_{i} = N\left( {0,{{ \sigma }}_{0} } \right),$$\end{document}εi=N0,σ0,which corresponds to the assumption of normally distributed residuals with homogeneous variance.

In our analysis, models were used in which the variance was allowed to be a linear function of some predictor variables z (which might be the same or different from the predictors x of the mean in Eq. 1), i.e.:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
